Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12} into ½-inch pieces. Toss on a #baking sheet{}
with large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack
until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(thinly sliced). Halve
@lemon{1}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @apricot jam{2}, @chicken stock concentrate{1},
@ancho chili powder{1/2}, and @water{1/4%cup}.

In a second small bowl, combine shallot, juice from lemon halves,
@sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of salt. Set aside, stirring occasionally, until
ready to serve.

Pat @chicken fillet{12} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and
pepper. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through,
~{5-7%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{}. Add jam mixture to pan and
cook until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat; stir in
@butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt and pepper.

In a large #bowl{}, toss together @mixed greens{2}, pickled shallot (and
pickling liquid), a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, and a pinch of salt and
pepper.

Divide potatoes, chicken, and salad between plates. Top chicken with sauce and
serve.

> Speaking of, we're serving up a side of crispy roasted potatoes that wouldn't say no to some of this smoky sauce.